<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BD08FA7B-788B-4285-9548-0F120F97465D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys Carvalho 1959:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Simpsonichthys de Carvalho</taxonomicName>
is a speciose assemblage of Neotropical aplocheiloid annual killifishes, comprising 43 species from an area encompassing northeastern, central and eastern South America (Costa, in press). It includes several well-corroborated clades, often diagnosed by unique morphological characters (Costa, 1996, 2003, in press). The 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus</taxonomicName>
species group, diagnosed by a derived frontal squamation, includes seven species: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus (Costa, Lacerda &amp; Brasil)</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EF5088C8-DD0A-40DC-BE9A-1D7EE399B7A8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys radiosus Costa &amp; Brasil 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="radiosus">S. radiosus Costa &amp; Brasil</taxonomicName>
, from the Tocantins River basin and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellatus">S. stellatus (Costa &amp; Brasil)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:18CCA4BB-6D66-4288-8A7E-DDDCE377B762" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys rufus Costa, Nielsen &amp; de Luca 2001:29" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufus">S. rufus Costa, Nielsen &amp; De Luca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trilineatus">S. trilineatus (Costa &amp; Brasil)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F7F23E1E-43B7-4C5B-8867-BDFBF5675CD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys auratus Costa &amp; Nielsen 2000:8" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">S. auratus Costa &amp; Nielsen</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2D6458F5-F74B-44D9-AEAE-99DBA1177C83" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys similis Costa &amp; Hellner 1999:90" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="similis">S. similis Costa &amp; Hellner</taxonomicName>
, from the rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Francisco River basin in Brazil and (Costa &amp; Brasil, 2004; Costa, in press). A new species of this group is herein described.
</paragraph>
